The paper discusses a toolkit for learning and inference with probabilistic models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The emphasis on learning tractable models suggests a focus on efficient algorithms and data structures, which are also relevant to data structures (cs.DS). The use of graphical models and algorithms for inference suggest a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
